A number of commenters have asked if OWU accepts public funding. The answer is no, it does not. This does not mean that students do not recieve federal student aid. The Supreme Court ruled, in the mid 1980's, that Federal Student Aid does not constitute federal support of religious universities, and that students can use their student aid at any accredited school to pursue any degree they choose. OWU is consistently ranked as a top academic universtiy in America.

Mainstream media is losing credibility in the Philippines. People are resorting to social media for information. CNN has portrayed Duterte negatively by reporting the news out of context. Philippine mainstream media too always looks for the smallest negative item about the president and overblows it, totally negating the many positive changes he has made in the 6 months that he has been in office. Just look at the declining circulation of Phil mainstream newspapers and the low engagement of online pages of mainstream media and you'll know that they are losing followers and importantly, integrity and credibility.
